In most cases in the FQI list, type varieties are not listed, but the rating of the species applies to the type variety when additional varieties are independently rated. However, as treated in FNA (Kartesz and Weakley appear to agree) Cerastium velutinum var. velutinum has different habitat than var. villosissimum, possibly less conservative. It appears that velutinum var. velutinum was not rated independently. Plus PA flora thinks velutinum var. velutinum is an exotic waif, while Kartesz maps it extensively in the state.
